  27 Dec 2014; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3.ebuild:
  Depend on activerecord for tests rather than rails so ppc and ppc64 can be
  added back, since their removal breaks the tree. They have activerecord
  keyworded but not rails itself.

  27 Dec 2014; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3.ebuild:
  Build dependencies are only needed for testing. Fix testing dependencies.
  Drop ppc and ppc64 keywords that could never have worked. The code fails with
  Rails 4.1, so avoid that version.

  16 Aug 2014; Anthony G. Basile <blueness@gentoo.org>
  activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3.ebuild:
  Keyword on ~ppc and ~ppc64, request by mrueg

  21 Apr 2014; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3.ebuild:
  Add ruby20, ruby21.

  11 Mar 2014; Johannes Huber <johu@gentoo.org>
  activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3.ebuild:
  ~x86 added, bug #487206

  13 Oct 2013; Markus Meier <maekke@gentoo.org>
  activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3.ebuild:
  add ~arm, bug #487206

*activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3 (07 Oct 2013)

  07 Oct 2013; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org>
  +activerecord-deprecated_finders-1.0.3.ebuild, +metadata.xml:
  Initial import for Rails 4.
